AI Teacher and Evaluator

This simple web application allows you to interact with the OpenAI GPT-3 API to generate feedback and evaluations for teacher's prompts and student responses.
Getting Started

Follow these steps to run the application on your local machine:

    Clone the Repository

    Clone this repository to your local machine using Git:

    bash

git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo.git

Navigate to the Directory

Change your working directory to the project folder:

bash

cd your-repo

Install Dependencies

Install the necessary Python packages using pip:

bash

pip install -r requirements.txt

Set Up Your OpenAI API Key

Before running the application, you need to set your OpenAI API key. Open the app.py file and locate the api_key variable. Replace None with your actual OpenAI API key:

python

api_key = "your-api-key"

Run the Application

Start the Flask application by running the following command:

bash

python app.py

You should see a message indicating that the application is running.

Access the Application

Open your web browser and visit http://127.0.0.1:5000/. This will take you to the AI Teacher and Evaluator application.

Set Your OpenAI API Key

On the web page, you will be prompted to enter your OpenAI API key. This is a one-time setup, and you'll only need to do it once.

Choose a Teacher's Question to Prompt

Select a question from the dropdown list. This question will be used as a prompt to generate a student response.

Assess the Evaluation and Suggestion

After selecting a question, click the "Generate Feedback" button. The application will provide you with an evaluation and suggestion based on the student's response.
